@NODE "INSTALL" "Installation of HTML Tools"
@{u}Installation:@{uu}

Pretty simple. Just drag the directory to wherever you want it.

@{"Back" link MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "FADING" "Creating Fading Colored Text With HTML Tools"
@{u}Creating Fading Colored Text With HTML Tools:@{uu}

First, double click on the HTMLTools icon, or use the shell if you prefer.
The following menu will appear:

Welcome to Nate's HTML tools!
Enter menu option
1) Fading HTML text
2) Graphics text
v) Verbose mode=0
p) Path="work:html/construction/"
q) Quit

type 1 and [enter].

Enter whatever sentence/title/insult/etc... you want to colorize.

Enter the name of the file you want to save it to,
   including .html extension.
      (The path will already be set to "work:html/construction/".
      To change this, you need to hit 'P' at the main menu.)

Enter a value between 0 and 255 to start the color counter.
   (0=dark, 255=bright)

Enter a value between 0 and 255 to stop the color counter.
   (0=dark, 255=bright)

Enter the fading values for the color red:
   1=fade from dark to bright
   0=fade from bright to dark
   2-257= the color value to sit at through the sentence, 2 if you don't use
          red.

Enter the same for green and blue.

Enter the font size you want.

The program will tell you where the file is saved, and you can open it with
Ed or another text editor from there for editing.

@{"Back" link MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "GRAPHICS" "Creating Graphical Text With HTML Tools"
@{u}Creating Graphical Text With HTML Tools:@{uu}

First, double click on the HTMLTools icon, or use the shell if you prefer.
The following menu will appear:

Welcome to Nate's HTML tools!
Enter menu option
1) Fading HTML text
2) Graphics text
v) Verbose mode=0
p) Path="work:html/construction/"
q) Quit

type 2 and [enter].

Enter the sentence or whatever you want to turn into text.

Enter the directory where youre letter images are stored.
   (The letters a-z/0-9 MUST be stored in a separate images directory
   named a.gif, b.gif, etc...)

Enter the filename, including .html extension if desired, to save the file to.
   (Do not include the full path name. To change that, hit P on the main menu)

Enter the extension of the graphics files. (.PNG, .GIF, .JPG, etc...)

Enter the pictures width in pixels. (All files must have the same width.
   You don't have to have the same width as the picture, but that can
   confuse some browsers)

Enter the same for height.

The program will then write the HTML code for the phrase. If it can't find an
   individual letter/number, it will warn you about it.

After this, you can edit the file using your favorite text editor.

@{"Back" link MAIN}
@ENDNODE
@NODE "FUTURE" "Future Plans For Development"
@{u}Future Plans For Development:@{uu}

1) MUI interface instead of cheesy shell interface.

2) More cool effects to do.

3) Automatically read and edit existing HTML files.

4) Perhaps a wizard to automatically publish HTML files. Not likely, though.

